00:48:12.570 --> 00:48:14.970
So it's not just that people don't know,

00:48:14.970 --> 00:48:18.840
but there is disinformation
being produced.

00:48:18.840 --> 00:48:22.230
- I see a couple of issues tied into this.

00:48:22.230 --> 00:48:25.830
One is that, people don't feel empowered

00:48:25.830 --> 00:48:27.210
to make the decision for themselves.

00:48:27.210 --> 00:48:29.050
They believe in something because

00:48:29.050 --> 00:48:30.850
they believe the person who's saying it

00:48:30.850 --> 00:48:34.980
rather than their own
ability to analyze it.

00:48:34.980 --> 00:48:39.500
But I also see a lot of
science communication issues

00:48:39.500 --> 00:48:41.580
that feed into this.

00:48:41.580 --> 00:48:44.010
One is the way scientists
talk about things.

00:48:44.010 --> 00:48:45.780
We talk about our uncertainty.

00:48:45.780 --> 00:48:48.840
When we go to give a
result to a colleague,

00:48:48.840 --> 00:48:52.260
we never start by saying, I think this.

00:48:52.260 --> 00:48:54.610
We start by saying, I
set out the experiment

00:48:54.610 --> 00:48:56.570
and I considered these variables,

00:48:56.570 --> 00:48:59.420
and I recognize this level of uncertainty

00:48:59.420 --> 00:49:02.650
and, given all this, it
suggests that the answer is X.

00:49:02.650 --> 00:49:06.250
When a scientist says,
the data suggests this,

00:49:06.250 --> 00:49:08.330
that's actually an
extremely strong statement

00:49:08.330 --> 00:49:10.220
from a scientist.

00:49:10.220 --> 00:49:12.730
But that's not the way
it's heard by other people.

00:49:12.730 --> 00:49:15.480
When we talk that way, we start by saying,

00:49:15.480 --> 00:49:16.820
here's all the uncertainty.

00:49:16.820 --> 00:49:18.630
Here's all the things that aren't known.

00:49:18.630 --> 00:49:21.200
The non-scientist hears
this message and goes,

00:49:21.200 --> 00:49:22.570
they don't know what
they're talking about.

00:49:22.570 --> 00:49:24.230
They're hearing the uncertainty?

00:49:24.230 --> 00:49:26.842
So that's a chunk in how it's done.

00:49:26.842 --> 00:49:30.300
And, what I did with the city,

00:49:30.300 --> 00:49:33.080
and that's the whole process
of doing the scenario

00:49:33.080 --> 00:49:36.150
as opposed to probabilities
of earthquake occurrence,

00:49:36.150 --> 00:49:38.290
I'm focusing on what we know,

00:49:38.290 --> 00:49:40.240
which are the consequences
of the disaster,

00:49:40.240 --> 00:49:42.080
rather than on what we don't know,

00:49:42.080 --> 00:49:44.410
which is when it's going to occur.

00:49:44.410 --> 00:49:47.654
So, as scientists, we're more interested

00:49:47.654 --> 00:49:50.660
in what we don't know, 'cause
that's where the research is.

00:49:50.660 --> 00:49:52.880
So, exactly what percentage
of climate change

00:49:52.880 --> 00:49:54.640
comes from human activity?

00:49:54.640 --> 00:49:56.560
That's an interesting scientific question.

00:49:56.560 --> 00:49:58.560
But when you talk about it that way,

00:49:58.560 --> 00:50:01.550
you aren't emphasizing that, in fact,

00:50:01.550 --> 00:50:05.570
a big chunk, we know
comes from human activity.

00:50:05.570 --> 00:50:06.403
We know.

00:50:07.290 --> 00:50:08.520
But we don't say it that way

00:50:08.520 --> 00:50:10.160
because, as scientists, we communicate.

00:50:10.160 --> 00:50:13.930
The other issue is that we need to,

00:50:13.930 --> 00:50:15.240
The sociologists tell us that

00:50:15.240 --> 00:50:19.790
when you give a problem without a solution

00:50:19.790 --> 00:50:23.600
you increase anxiety and
reduce the ability to act.

00:50:23.600 --> 00:50:25.590
If you want people to take action,

00:50:25.590 --> 00:50:27.140
you need to combine the pro,

00:50:27.140 --> 00:50:29.830
you give the problem,
here's what you do about it.

00:50:29.830 --> 00:50:32.670
And, that's what happened
with me in Los Angeles.

00:50:32.670 --> 00:50:35.100
I said, here's the problem
and here's what we can do.

00:50:35.100 --> 00:50:37.200
Fix these buildings, get this water.

00:50:37.200 --> 00:50:39.323
On climate change, we need to say,

00:50:40.530 --> 00:50:42.590
The scientists are uncomfortable saying

00:50:42.590 --> 00:50:44.460
it's somebody else's
job how to deal with it.

00:50:44.460 --> 00:50:46.020
We know we gotta reduce carbon,

00:50:46.020 --> 00:50:47.660
but that's somebody else's job.

00:50:47.660 --> 00:50:50.870
Whereas, I think if we say,
